President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed May 21 through May 27, 2023, as National Emergency Medical Services Week. In his proclamation, President Biden acknowledges the courage and sacrifices made by EMS providers across the country, especially during the pandemic. He emphasizes the importance of supporting and caring for those who care for us, highlighting the administration's efforts to help EMS providers by providing resources, improving training, and addressing student debt through the Public Service Loan Forgiveness program. The proclamation also recognizes the vital role of EMS providers in saving lives and calls upon the nation to honor and pay tribute to these brave workers.